<br>
We killed the Lord 15 times in one session.  I DID NOT get the kind of drop rates you guys were mentioning on the wingblade or even close.  It appears that he drops some sort of weapon about 50% of the time.  And it appears that there are at least 4 weapons which can drop (some monk fists, a staff, windblade, and another sword, so from that you can reduce the odds by another 25%).   Out of 15 kills we had 1 wingblade drop. That comes out to about a 7% drop rate.  We also killed him 4x's earlier and no wingblades dropped.  So I think the 50% drop rate quote is a bit outdated or something screwy is going on with our server.<br>
<br>
We had a bit less than 3 groups in attendance, average level was around 59.  If you have a good showing don't even waste you time with any fancy FD pulling or splitting.  We found the best method was just to pull the first thing you can find opposite the Lord and Gaurdian and deal with it.  I think we had 2 vanquishers and about 4 lesser spirocs come on the pull, all easily mezzable.  They hit for crap and are easy to deal with.  We had 3 chanters which had no problems keeping things under control.  The key is to kill Vanquishers first, finish killing off the lessers, leave the gaurdian up, and kill the Lord until you get what you want.  The vanquisher which runs between the Lord and the Gaurdian was the most difficult for use to get.  We took a couple of DTs from the lord trying to gain agro from the last Vanquisher.<br>
<br>
Assume at least 2 deaths per Lord pull depending how much fire power you have.  The first death being on the initial pull, then one during the fight.  We had an enchanter chain agro the lord 30 secs into the fight to gain agro and take the DT, so tanks could keep him occupied until nukers could finish him off.  Killing him fast (which means Wiz/Mag support) is key to reducing how many DTs you take over the course of the battle.  Also DA will not work against the DT so don't even waste your time trying.  Just account the DT's into the pull plan.<br>
<br>
One thing we did do was the initial kill on the side of the island with the port in.  Sirran will spawn.  On next two pulls or until Sirran despawns pull to center back of island just over the hill so Sirran doesn't agro.  When you see him go poof, then move camp back to port in so he will respawn out of the way.  Sirran will not respawn each time the Lord is killed, if he is already up from a previous kill.<br>
<br>
I recommend bringing a CR summoning team with you (Wiz,Cleric,Necro) so you can add re-enforcments if you get low.  The first time we did this several weeks ago we didn't have 2 extra people to spare on taking the DTs and we had no way to bring up help.<br>
<br>
The hardest think about this camp for us was keeping people in the raid for the entire duration.  <br>
<br>
Good luck to you.<br>
